{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01TtsFRCQTnnChoRPoSGVZRk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WoMzkS5Ktj5sMUEDKiohqd","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/findings.txt <<'EOF'\nSPARK-PI NAMESPACE COMPLIANCE AUDIT\nDate: 2026-06-18  |  Scope: namespace spark-pi  |  Mode: read-only audit (no changes made)\n\n=== CORRECTLY CONFIGURED (PASS) ===\n1. Dedicated ServiceAccount: workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job)\n   run under the dedicated 'spark-pi' ServiceAccount, not 'default'. PASS.\n2. RBAC scoped to namespace: permissions granted via a namespaced Role\n   (spark-pi-role) + RoleBinding (spark-pi-role-binding), not a ClusterRole.\n   RoleBinding subject correctly targets ServiceAccount spark-pi. PASS.\n3. Resource governance: all three workloads (master, worker, job) define both\n   CPU/memory requests (200m / 512Mi) and limits (500m / 1Gi). No unbounded\n   containers. PASS.\n4. Image tag pinning: all workloads use apache/spark:3.5.3 (an explicit version\n   tag, not ':latest'), consistent across master, worker, and job. PASS.\n\n=== GAPS / FINDINGS (FAIL or WARN) ===\nF1 [HIGH] No Pod/container securityContext hardening. spark-master, spark-worker,\n   and the spark-pi job all have securityContext: {} (empty). Missing:\n   runAsNonRoot, runAsUser, allowPrivilegeEscalation: false, readOnlyRootFilesystem,\n   and capabilities.drop: [ALL]. Containers therefore run as root (apache/spark\n   default UID 0) with full default capabilities. Violates least-privilege /\n   restricted Pod Security Standard.\nF2 [MEDIUM] RBAC over-permission + config drift. Live spark-pi-role grants verbs\n   create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on services, configmaps,\n   persistentvolumeclaims AND pods. The kubectl last-applied-configuration only\n   declared services/configmaps/persistentvolumeclaims (NO pods) -> the live Role\n   has drifted from its declared manifest; 'pods' was added out-of-band. Broad\n   write verbs (delete/update/patch) on these resources exceed what a SparkPi\n   batch job needs.\nF3 [MEDIUM] No NetworkPolicy. The namespace has zero NetworkPolicy objects, so\n   all pod ingress/egress is unrestricted (default-allow). No network isolation\n   for the Spark master (7077/8080) or worker.\nF4 [LOW] Image provenance not cryptographically pinned. Images use a mutable tag\n   (apache/spark:3.5.3) from public Docker Hub with no digest (@sha256:) pin and\n   no private/trusted-registry sourcing. Tag is mutable; provenance unverifiable.\n\n=== ENVIRONMENT SNAPSHOT ===\nPods: spark-master (Running), spark-worker (Running), spark-pi (Completed).\nConfigMaps: only kube-root-ca.crt (system). NetworkPolicies: none.\nServiceAccounts: default (unused by workloads), spark-pi (in use).\n\nNOTE: This is an audit report only. No remediation was performed; the live\nconfiguration is unchanged. Remediation to be planned separately.\nEOF\nkubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat /tmp/findings.txt)\" 2>&1\necho \"--- verify ---\"\nkubectl -n spark-pi get configmap config-audit -o jsonpath='{.data.findings\\.txt}' 2>&1 | head -5\necho; echo \"--- bytes ---\"\nkubectl -n spark-pi get configmap config-audit -o jsonpath='{.data.findings\\.txt}' | wc -c","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap and verify"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2222,"cache_read_input_tokens":29498,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2222},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"03858f41-152a-409d-a21c-2d1fe0cb7eda","uuid":"28c84b13-14c2-4281-ab28-83873177dff8","request_id":"req_011CcAWsWeyGZ3xFeR6RQYgZ"}
